Program: Discovery
Title: Nitric oxide - the new wonder drug
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwgl
Last Broadcast Date: 05 June 1995
How nitric oxide, once considered poisonous, could be a future wonder drug. The role of nitric oxide is in helping keep blood pressure stable and in killing bacteria and parasites; changing its role from pollutant to possible medicine. Also in the programme, why scientists are rethinking climate-change models and an update on the TB vaccine. Show less